snippet.textDisplay: That jaws blood would have been done with metaballs. From Wikipedia "metaballs are organic-looking n-dimensional isosurfaces, characterised by their ability to meld together when in close proximity to create single, contiguous objects." Been around since 1980. I've used them back in the day. If you see globby CGI blood in an old movie it's most likely metaballs.

snippet.textDisplay:
Sandberg seems like a nice guy, but I don't think I could ever forgive him for endorsing that Annabelle: Creation fan film 'competition'.
If you don't know, Warner Bros ran a competition for people to submit their own 'spin off' short films and they could win a week trip to Hollywood, meet Sandberg and explore the studio.
However, the small print stated that any of the ideas in the short films were the property of Warner Bros as soon as the short film was submitted, and no attribution or credit had to be given to the original creator (let alone profits/a cut of money).
Also, the studio trip was an empty promise, as the small print also stated that the 'week' trip could also be shortened to just one day, and Sandberg could be busy on the day that they pick, so you weren't even guaranteed to meet him.
Super scummy movie studio stuff.

snippet.textDisplay:
In terms of video game cinematics I can think of a few.

To be honest any of the WoW cinematic trailers will do but some nice ones of note for techniques they nailed are:
- Wrath of the Lich King (ice and snow)

- Mists of Pandaria (fur)
- Warlords of Draenor (fire & skin)
- Legion (water and destruction)
- Shadowlands (ice and snow again)


The Elder Scrolls online trailers are all very good.


I have a softspot for the Dynasty Warriors cg trailers as well as they are so ridiculous it's hilarious!
